# Sample override for the base-map server ("Soulmask Server", Level01_Main).
# Currently STOPPED — see SOULMASK.md §9 for the revival plan: this server's
# allocations (8777/27015/18888) collide with the running DLC server and
# must be changed (e.g. 8778/27016/18889), it needs a steamcmd update, and
# cluster wiring (-serverid=, -mainserverport=/-clientserverconnect=) added
# to its Startup Command in the Pterodactyl panel before it can safely run
# alongside the DLC server.
#
# To activate: copy this file to
#   31e20408-2a4e-42be-b97d-877275fc2b96.env
# (drop the .example suffix) and uncomment below once the instance is
# revived as a cluster CLIENT of the DLC server (b87c0a5b…, ROLE=main).
#
# ROLE=client
#
# Shares the tmpfs pak copy with the main instance — same depot, byte-
# identical pak file (verified, SOULMASK.md §9).
# PAK_RAMDISK=1
#
# Leave SOULMASK_MIN/LOW/HIGH/WRITEBACK at instance-defaults.env's values
# unless this instance's hot set is measured to differ from the DLC
# server's (MEASUREMENTS.md M1) — a second ~6G hot set on a 16G host is
# already tight (SOULMASK.md §9 "Resource reality check"), so do not widen
# these without also re-checking system.slice headroom in setup-cgroups.sh.
